<b>Chèvre chaud</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../002/11002.xml">
French</link> dish, consisting of <link>
Chèvre cheese</link> served hot. It is usually made by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../987/52987.xml">
broiling</link> the Chèvre cheese on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../969/36969.xml">
French bread</link>, and is often served with a green <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../950/61950.xml">
salad</link>, and accompanied by <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../705/12635705.xml">
vinaigrette</link>, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../478/22478.xml">
olive oil</link> or <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../398/847398.xml">
balsamic vinegar</link>.



